[thinking] **Clarifying test class structure**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether to subclass a public static class, but I wonder if putting that inside a test is okay. The rule states to avoid using "$" in test class names. It seems all top-level public classes are acceptable, but I’m unsure about inner test helpers since they compile into a different format. I think it might be safer to keep things separate and avoid subclassing. Instead, I could use StandardLogger with ByteArrayOutputStream in my test case to assert the logger's behavior.
